cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SAFE-CARE Bench, please cite it using this metadata."
title: "SAFE-CARE Bench: A Reproducible Benchmark for Safety, Guardrails, and User Experience in Multi-Turn Healthcare AI Agent Conversations"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Eltayeb
    given-names: Yassen
    affiliation: Conefia
    email: dev@conefia.com
  - family-names: Hafez
    given-names: Monzir
    affiliation: Conefia
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-19
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/Conefia/SAFE-CARE-Bench"
abstract: >
  A reproducible benchmark for evaluating safety, guardrails, and user experience in
  multi-turn healthcare AI agent conversations. Uses a controlled A0-A4 ablation design
  in which five agent variants differing only by active capability layer are scored over
  identical simulated conversations with synthetic personas. Scoring spans six Likert
  dimensions and two binary dimensions, with separate single-turn and multi-turn safety
  and escalation judges, and a hard-fail override on missed escalation. Companion
  instrument to the SAFE-CARE framework for healthcare AI agent design and evaluation.
keywords:
  - healthcare AI
  - AI agents
  - evaluation
  - benchmark
  - ablation study
  - LLM-as-judge
  - guardrails
  - safety
  - multi-turn dialogue
  - retrieval-augmented generation
references:
  - type: generic
    title: "SAFE-CARE: A Framework for Designing and Evaluating Safe Healthcare AI Agents"
    authors:
      - family-names: Eltayeb
        given-names: Yassen
        affiliation: Conefia
    doi: "10.5281/zenodo.21330841"
    year: 2026
    notes: "SAFE-CARE Bench is the evaluation instrument for the Evaluate principle of this framework."

